  <description><![CDATA[<p>Set a few minutes’ walk outside the bustling resort of Ischia Town, the Grand Hotel Punta Molino offers a relaxing seaside escape. Set above a sandy bay, the five star hotel has been carefully designed to fit in with the landscape whilst making the most of the cliffside sea views.  Rooms here are decorated in a typical style with vietri tiles and large windows or a balcony with garden or sea views.</p>
<p>The fantastic restaurants and shops of Ischia Town make for a great evening out but you can also experience an excellent evening at the hotel’s restaurant La Terraza where you can sample local food whilst enjoying panoramic views. Those wanting to relax can enjoy the two outdoor swimming pools (open April to October), one freshwater and one which uses the island’s natural thermal water, and the small sandy beach (open May to October) that’s equipped with sun loungers and a bar. For the ultimate in relaxation though, we recommend heading to the spa where you’ll find a further thermal pool and a range of beauty treatments to enjoy.</p>]]></description>
